    {
      "id": "RQ-0069",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Validate runner session IDs before persisting them",
      "description": "Session-id recovery accepts broad JSON keys and scans all stdout, which can persist unrelated IDs from runner chatter. Goal: only store IDs from runner-specific session-start/resume events and preserve last known-good state when output is ambiguous.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "session",
        "typing",
        "reliability"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/json.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/process/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/continue_session.rs",
        "make agent-ci"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/json.rs:21-39 parses the first JSON object starting at the first '{' in any line as a compatibility fallback.",
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/json.rs:42-58 accepts type=session id plus generic thread_id, session_id, or sessionID without runner/event-shape validation.",
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/process/mod.rs:260-265 falls back to scanning full stdout for a session id if the streaming reader did not capture one.",
        "A wrong stored session id can make future continue paths retry invalid state before falling back, adding user-visible recovery noise.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define runner-specific accepted session event shapes and ID validation rules for each supported runner.",
        "Use the structured stream-captured session id as authoritative; make full-stdout fallback opt-in and shape-validated.",
        "Preserve the previous known-good session id when output contains ambiguous JSON but no confirmed session event.",
        "Add tests with log lines containing unrelated thread_id/session_id fields and confirmed session-start events.",
        "Verify by running cargo test -p ralph runner::execution and make agent-ci."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan finding",
      "created_at": "2026-04-29T03:24:54Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-29T03:24:54Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
