        "make macos-test-contracts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceOperationalHealth.swift:274-288 treats idle/watching/stopped as no issue and starting as info.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceOperationalHealth.swift:288-304 maps QueueWatcherHealth.State.degraded to severity .warning even when nextRetryAt is present and recovery is still scheduled.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceOperationalHealth.swift:305-314 maps exhausted failed state to severity .error, which is the appropriate operator-visible terminal state.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Change degraded watcher health with a future nextRetryAt to info or neutral status rather than warning.",
        "Keep warning/error severity for degraded-without-retry or failed states that need operator attention.",
        "Ensure the operational summary and quick actions use the new severity consistently and include retry schedule details only in diagnostics/logs.",
        "Add watcher-health tests for starting, degraded-with-retry, degraded-without-retry, and failed summaries.",
        "Verify by running the focused watcher health tests or make macos-test-contracts, then make agent-ci."
      ],
